    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-01-30T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-01-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.51/611a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-01-30T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 30, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>77. Please endeavor, through discreet inquiry, to ascertain (<hi rend="italic"
                        >a</hi>) whether British banks or firms are now extending credits, short
                    term or otherwise, to Japanese interests, (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) the method
                    employed to “peg” the yen to the pound sterling and (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)
                    if the method employed is the maintenance of gold or other deposits in British
                    banks, whether credits are extended thereon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
